{{!-- Stat Block Importer Dialog --}}
<form class="rt-stat-block-importer">
  <div class="rt-import-instructions">
    <p><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-info"></i> Paste a stat block from a PDF, book, or other source below. The parser will attempt to extract:</p>
    <ul class="rt-import-features">
      <li><i class="fa-solid fa-check"></i> Characteristics (WS, BS, S, T, Ag, Int, Per, WP, Fel)</li>
      <li><i class="fa-solid fa-check"></i> Wounds and Movement</li>
      <li><i class="fa-solid fa-check"></i> Skills with bonuses (+10, +20)</li>
      <li><i class="fa-solid fa-check"></i> Armour value</li>
      <li><i class="fa-solid fa-check"></i> Threat Level</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="rt-import-note"><i class="fa-solid fa-triangle-exclamation"></i> Talents, Traits, and Weapons require manual addition after import.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="rt-import-field">
    <label for="statblock">
      <i class="fa-solid fa-paste"></i> Stat Block Text
    </label>
    <textarea name="statblock" rows="12" placeholder="Paste stat block here...

Example format:
WS  BS  S   T   Ag  Int Per WP  Fel
35  30  40  45  25  20  30  35  15

Wounds: 15
Movement: 3/6/9/18
Armour: 4 (All)

Skills: Awareness +10, Dodge, Intimidate +20
Talents: Swift Attack, Combat Master
Traits: Dark Sight, Natural Armour (2)"></textarea>
  </div>

  <div class="rt-import-tips">
    <details>
      <summary><i class="fa-solid fa-lightbulb"></i> Parsing Tips</summary>
      <ul>
        <li>Characteristic lines can be in table format or "WS: 35, BS: 30" format</li>
        <li>Skills should include bonuses like "Dodge +10" or "Parry +20"</li>
        <li>Movement can be "3/6/9/18" or "Half 3, Full 6, Charge 9, Run 18"</li>
        <li>The parser works best with clean text - avoid special characters</li>
      </ul>
    </details>
  </div>
</form>
